The American people are not interested in staged production signing ceremonies, they want an agreement that will create good paying jobs in America and heal economic injustices suffered for the past three decades. 

My statement on Trump's #NAFTA:   https://kaptur.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/kaptur-statement-signing-us-mexico-and-canada-trade-agreement-president … (3/3)

Congress will have the final say on trade. 

And @realDonaldTrump's campaign promises to working people and the reality of his #NAFTA only reinforce this Administration’s standard: Say one thing, do another. (2/3)

The same week GM announced the idling of five U.S. facilities and cutting 15,000 living wage jobs, including in Lordstown, Ohio, @POTUS has claimed premature victory as U.S., Canadian and Mexican officials signed a tentative replacement for #NAFTA. (1/3)
Watch our full press conference here:  https://www.facebook.com/RepresentativeMarcyKaptur/videos/290252891613102/ … https://twitter.com/RepMarcyKaptur/status/1068143842640232448 …

At 9:30 AM I'll be standing with my colleagues @RepTimRyan @RepDebDingell @RepLawrence @repsandylevin at a press conference calling on @POTUS to act and for GM to keep good paying jobs in the US. 

We need a fair playing field for workers.

WATCH HERE:  https://www.facebook.com/RepresentativeMarcyKaptur …
